{
  "texts": [
    "Now let us study the action of such a split 2-group on line operators.",
    "Acting just by the 0-form symmetry, the line operators must form 2-representations of G (0).",
    "Let us pick a line operator L participating in a 2-representation G (0) such that H L ⊆ G (0) descends to an induced 0-form symmetry of L with a 't Hooft anomaly [σ] ∈ H 2 (H L, ×): ρ (2) = (H L, [σ]).",
    "Now, we ask what are the possible characters χ L ∈ G (1) of G (1) that L can carry.",
    "Since H L leaves L invariant, we must haveχ L (γ) = χ L (α h (γ)),(162)for all h ∈ H L and γ ∈ G (1)."
  ]
}